p2
VTribute to Tyagaraja
p3
sVnews
p4
VEminent musicians presented concerts at the 164th aradhana of Sri Tyagaraja organised jointly by the Sri Sadguru Tyagabrahma Aradhana Trust and Sri Sathguru Sangeetha Sabha, Tiruchi, for four days recently.P.K. Thiagarajan, chairman, board of trustees, Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple, Srirangam, presided over the inaugural function and Parur M.S. Anantharaman, violin vidwan, who inaugurated the festival, was felicitated on the occasion.Cleveland V.V. Sundaram, released the souvenir and writer Prema Nandakumar offered felicitations.Rituals and eventsSpecial abishekam followed by Veda parayanam for the saint was performed on all the four days. The event took place at the Kodiyalam Seshadri Iyengar Marriage Hall, South Devi Street, Srirangam, in the morning.This was followed by unchavriti bhajan by Sri Ramakrishna Hari group, Srirangam.The violin team comprising Parur Anantharaman, M.A. Sundareswaran, M.S. Anantha Sree, M.A. Krishnaswamy, M.K. Ananth Lakshmi and M.S. Ananthakrishnan presented the Nadhanjali on the inaugural day.They were ably assisted by K.V. Prasad on the mridangam and Tiruchi K. Murali on the ghatam. The first day's programme came to an end with Divyanama bhajan by O.S. Sundar and party.On the second day, Aishwarya, Koviladi R. Madhwa Prasad and Ranjani and Gayathri presented vocal concerts.Recitals of Saketharaman, Hyderabad Subbulakshmi, Tiruchi K. Ramesh and Sanjay Subramaniam took place on the third day.The final day's programme commenced with vocal concerts of Aparna Kumar and N. Vijay Siva.The festival concluded with the nagaswaram concert by Tirupati Subramanyam and Raviprabha party. The four-day aradhana concluded with Anjaneya utsavam.
